Societe Generale Seeks to Buy Lender Banka Celje, Finance Says

-- B y   B o r i s   C e r n i
-- 
2011-05-25T07:07:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/societe-generale-seeks-to-buy-lender-banka-celje-finance-says.html
Societe Generale (GLE)  SA is the sole
bidder for Slovenian lender Banka Celje d.d., offering 297
million euros ($417 million) in a non-binding bid, Finance
newspaper  reported , citing people familiar with the process it
didn’t name.  Due diligence for the purchase of Banka Celje, the seventh
biggest lender in Slovenia, will be completed by the end of
June, the Ljubljana-based newspaper said today.  Banka Celje is being sold by Nova Ljubljanska Banka d.d. as
the country’s biggest bank sells assets to improve its capital
base.  Societe Generale is already operating in Slovenia through
its unit SKB banka d.d.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Boris Cerni in Ljubljana, Slovenia, at 
 bcerni@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
